An opportunity has arisen for an Inorganic Chemistry Senior Analyst to join our busy Team within the Water Quality department. You will be based at our Farnborough Laboratory and will report to the Chemistry Manager.

The key purpose of this role is to perform, and provide advice and assistance to a team of 9 staff undertaking chemical testing using ICP, Colorimetry, Spectrophotometry and Ion Chromatography testing in accordance with the Laboratory Management System. The successful candidate will be required to work towards being the ‘competent person’ in line with DWI Regulation 16(2)(d)(i) of the Water Supply (Water Quality) Regulations requirements.

The role will work in a team of two Senior Analysts. They will have similar responsibilities for organisation of the Inorganic Chemistry section, preventative maintenance, troubleshooting on all instrumentation, authorisation of data produced by Inorganic Chemists, departmental stock control and ordering. They will also carry out annual appraisals, target setting and work performance of team members and assist the Senior Chemist with validation and development of Laboratory methods.

Main responsibilities will include:
Responsibility for day to day organisation and prioritisation of sample workload through the Inorganic Chemistry section;
Report to the Chemistry Manager on all chemistry/personnel issues;
Responsibility for preventative maintenance on instrumentation;
Organisation of training of staff on all relevant laboratory methods;
Responsible to ensure all Inorganic chemical testing is carried out in accordance with the Management System;
Ensure data is accurately entered into the Laboratory Information Management System within set timeframe;
Authorisation of data of subordinates and ensure all work is carried out to meet quality requirements;
To notify internally any issues relating to quality control of the testing;
Assist in developing and validating new Laboratory methods
To prepare solutions and chemicals in accordance with company internal procedures;
Quality Auditor of internal practices to ensure compliance to the management system.
Conduct yearly appraisals of relevant staff members, target setting and assessment of work performance;
Ensure use of equipment and chemicals are documented to allow adequate stock control
Be the Inorganic Chemistry competent person according to Regulation 16(2)(d)(i) of the Water Supply (Water Quality) Regulations and to actively pursue Continued Professional Development.

The successful candidate should:
Have existing knowledge and a proven track record of good laboratory practice, routine testing, instrument maintenance and troubleshooting gained via previous practical laboratory experience (at least 2 years)
Senior Staff should have a minimum academic qualification in an appropriate scientific subject such as NVQ level 3 or equivalent, and have full membership of a relevant professional body.
Hold excellent numeracy, literacy, computer literacy and laboratory skills – these are an essential requirement
Have a good working knowledge of the Water Supply (Water Quality) Regulations and ISO17025:2017 is essential.

Please note the successful candidates will be undertaking training in the first 3 weeks of employment, therefore you will be unable to take any annual leave or time off during this period.

The recruitment process may include an interview via Zoom and you may be asked to prepare a short presentation in advance of your interview, you may also be asked to complete a PPA Assessment (Personality Profile Assessment).

This post is subject to a basic criminal record check and Right to Work in the UK.

In return, we offer a competitive salary, a minimum of 25 days annual leave, a stakeholder pension scheme in which the maximum Company contribution is 10% and life assurance scheme.

Please note, we reserve the right to close or extend this position depending on application numbers. Therefore we would urge candidates to submit an application as early as possible.

