Frontiers, a leading Open Access Publisher and Open Science Platform, is looking for an enthusiastic and customer-oriented Application Support Analyst to provide user support and customer service on our public web site (www.frontiersin.org).

The Application Support Analyst will be responsible for troubleshoot problems and advise users on the appropriate action.

This full-time, permanent position in our London office will provide the successful candidate the opportunity to work in a stimulating, fast-paced work environment with an innovative scholarly publisher.

Responsibilities:
Provide superior assistance and service to all internal and external customers;
Respond promptly and courteously to support requests;
Prioritize requests according to criticality;
Identify timely and accurate solutions to technical issues;
Develop expertise in the everyday use of internally developed systems;
Provide day-to-day maintenance and support for our online publishing system;
Document all support activities in ticket tracking database;
Participate in maintaining Help Centre and team documentation;
Assistance on other projects as needed.
Requirements
Higher Education background in IT or previous application support experience;
Technical proficiency, with hands-on skills using ticketing systems;
Excellent communication skills in written and spoken English;
An outgoing, collaborative and professional personality;
Ability to work independently, be highly organized and meet deadlines;
A willingness to work in a fast-paced, target-driven environment.
Benefits
25 days' vacation per year and Christmas office closure
Participation into the company's annual bonus scheme
Frontiers has taken the decision to offer our employees full flexibility to work-from-home (within the country of employment) until the end of 2020.
Access to the latest equipment and international working environment
Professional development opportunities
Plenty of social and fun benefits
Christmas party, summer barbecue, monthly happy hour
Fruits and snacks in the kitchen as well as much tea & coffee as you like
In-house well being activities including free weekly yoga
How to apply
Please submit your application in English.
Applicants must be British or EU citizen or have a valid British work permit.
Agencies must first contact jobs@frontiersin.org and confirm agreement to our T&C’s, failing which any exclusivity and/or candidate representation right will be considered to be waived.
Frontiers actively embraces diversity and is a safe and welcoming workplace. Recruitment is free from discrimination - including based on race, national or ethnic origin, age, religion, disability, sex, gender identity or sexual orientation. With over 600 employees from more than 50 different nations, our diversity creates vibrant teams and constantly challenges us to appreciate multiple perspectives.
